Mxolisi Mngadi, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pietermaritzburg &ndash; A newborn baby has been found abandoned under the Dusi Bridge, near a canoe club in Pietermaritzburg, paramedics said on Friday. The baby boy was suffering from hypothermia, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said.Guards employed by B-Secure Security found the baby and began warming him up. He was taken to Edendale hospital and police were informed. &nbsp; Police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said a case of child abandonment has been opened for investigation by Alexandra Road police.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.